The driver can incorrectly send OP_QUERY to mongos with a read preference like:
{code}
{$readPreference:{mode:'secondary'}}
{code}
mongos 2.4 returns "BadValue: cannot canonicalize query". Later mongoses accept this format. Regardless, according to Server Selection Spec, if the query filter is empty it must be included anyway:
{code}
{$query:{}, $readPreference:{mode:'secondary'}}
{code}
This format works with all supported versions of mongos.

test_large_inserts_ordered fails with a 2.4 mongos. mongos responds to getLastError after an oversized insert:
{code}
	{ err: "assertion src/mongo/s/strategy_shard.cpp:461", n: 0, ok: 1.0 }
{code}
There's an "err" but no "code", so _mongoc_write_result_merge_legacy skips it. There may be more cases where the server returns an err with no code, audit all.

Converting a [DBRef|https://docs.mongodb.org/manual/reference/mongodb-extended-json/#db-reference] from JSON to BSON results in an ObjectId type:

{noformat}
{ "dbref": { "$ref": "collection", "$id": { "$oid": "56315a7c6118fd1b920270b1" }}}
{noformat}

Results in:

{noformat}
     0 : 18 00 00 00 07 64 62 72 65 66 00 56 31 5a 7c 61  [.....dbref.V1Z|a]
    10 : 18 fd 1b 92 02 70 b1 00                          [.....p..]
{noformat}

Peaking into {{bson-json.c}} revealed that libbson attempts to convert DBRef objects to deprecated DBPointer types. I'm not sure why an ObjectId is being generated, but even the intentional behavior seems incorrect.

DBRef objects should allow any value as their {{$id}} (obviously arrays cannot be IDs, but I assume the server only enforces this on documents' {{_id}} field value, not DBRefs). Additionally, DBRef objects may contain additional fields (e.g. {{$db}}, and any non-$-prefixed fields thereafter). Correct behavior would be to simply convert DBRef objects to embedded documents.

The driver will exit without writing data or reporting an error:
{code}
   max_wire_version = mongoc_cluster_node_max_wire_version (&client->cluster, hint);
   if (max_wire_version == -1) {
      EXIT;
   }
{code}
The checked call to _mongoc_client_preselect, above, should ensure max_wire_version is non-negative, so this should be an ALWAYS_ASSERT instead of a regular check?

/WriteCommand/bypass_validation fails on Solaris against a standalone or replica set with:
{code}
  not authorized on dbtest_1448377510_683 to execute command { insert: "bypass_1448377510_683", writeConcern: {}, ordered: true, bypassDocumentValidation: true, documents: 3 }
{code}
It passes on other platforms, and against a mongos on Solaris.

{code}
src/bson/bson-json.c: In function '_bson_json_read_end_map':
src/bson/bson-json.c:836:7: warning: enumeration value 'BSON_TYPE_DBPOINTER' not handled in switch [-Wswitch-enum]
